[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ben Gordon: Woking sign former Colchester and Chester left-back

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
National League side Woking have signed defender Ben Gordon on a one-year deal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 25-year-old left-back spent time in the youth set-ups at Leeds and Chelsea and has had stints at Ross County and Colchester United and Chester.
Gordon has also had loan spells at Kilmarnock, Scunthorpe, Peterborough, Birmingham and Yeovil.
Meanwhile, Charlie Carter, a 19-year-old midfielder who came through the club's academy, has agreed terms with the Cards for 2016-17.
